###fixing the audio delay issue at fresh installations (mainly wireplumber default sets 1~5 seconds idle)

###make a custom config:
>>>mkdir -p ~/.config/wireplumber/wireplumber.conf.d
>>>nano ~/.config/wireplumber/wireplumber.conf.d/disable-suspend.conf

###add into the nano file
>>>
```
monitor.alsa.rules = [
  {
    matches = [
      {
        node.name = "~alsa_output.*"
      }
    ]
    actions = {
      update-props = {
        session.suspend-timeout-seconds = 0
      }
    }
  }
]
```

### Restart the audio devices:
>>>systemctl --user restart wireplumber pipewire pipewire-pulse

